-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Reckitt Benckiser, Swatch Group, Kering
-- 
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 02:15AM EST
-- None



Dec 18 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including LVMH and Reckitt Benckiser, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Luxury Goods: Barclays cuts targets on LVMH <LVMH.PA>, others [ID:nWNAB05J4J] * Reckitt Benckiser <RB.L>: Jefferies cuts target price to 4800p from 5000p; rating hold * Legal & General <LGEN.L>: Jefferies starts with buy; price target 282p Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Adidas <ADSGn.DE>: Susquehanna cuts target price to 60 euros from 64 euros; rating neutral * Burberry <BRBY.L>: Barclays raises target price to 1635p from 1585p; rating equal weight * CGG <GEPH.PA>: Barclays re-instates coverage with underweight; price target 6.20 euros * Dixons Carphone <DC.L>: Barclays raises target price to 490p from 470p; rating overweight * Imagination Technologies <IMG.L>: Barclays raises target to 195p from 190p; underweight * Kering <PRTP.PA>: Barclays cuts target to 181 euros from 185 euros; rating overweight * Legal & General <LGEN.L>: Jefferies starts with buy; price target 282p * LVMH <LVMH.PA>: Barclays cuts target price to 152 euros from 154 euros; rating overweight * Reckitt Benckiser <RB.L>: Jefferies cuts target price to 4800p from 5000p; rating hold * Salvatore Ferragamo <SFER.MI>: Barclays cuts target to 24 euros from 25 euros; overweight